The children, believed to be between the ages of six and 16, were experiencing breathing problems after swimming. JOHANNESBURG - At least 33 children have been rushed to hospital after inhaling toxic fumes of pool acid that had been poured into the water at Zoo Lake in Johannesburg on Saturday afternoon.The children, believed to be between the ages of six and 16, were experiencing breathing problems after swimming. No fatalities have been reported and investigations are underway to determine the cause of the incident.ER24 s Chitra Bodasing Harduth said, At this stage the children are believed to be in a minor condition, having reported difficulty in breathing. _EDITOR S NOTE: Paramedics earlier reported that 33 children were involved in the incident but Community Development MMC Nonhlanhla Sifumba has subsequently clarified that only 20 children were affected. _